Usage
1. Clone or Download the Repository:
To get started, first clone or download the tool from GitHub:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/Lt-Spl4sh/Grim-Reapers.git
2. Navigate to the Tool's Directory:
Once you've downloaded or cloned the repository, navigate into the Grim-Reapers folder:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd Grim-Reapers
3. Install Dependencies:
Make sure you have Python 3.x installed on your system, then install the necessary dependencies using pip:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Running the Tool:
To run the tool, use the following command:

bash
Copy
Edit
python GrimReapers.py
This will start the Grim Reapers multi-tool and display the main menu.

5. Main Menu Options:
When the tool starts, you'll be presented with the following menu:

markdown
Copy
Edit
1. IP Lookup
2. Subdomain Finder
3. Port Scanner
4. Phishing Page (WIP)
5. Vulnerability Scanner
99. Brute-Force Login
00. Exit
6. Using Each Option:
IP Lookup: Enter an IP address or domain to get geolocation and other details.

Subdomain Finder: Enter a domain name to find common subdomains.

Port Scanner: Enter an IP address to check open ports.

Phishing Page: A placeholder for phishing simulation (work in progress).

Vulnerability Scanner: Enter a URL to check for common vulnerabilities like SQL injection.

Brute-Force Login: Choose a wordlist file (in .txt format) from the toolâ€™s directory and attempt a brute-force login to a provided URL.

7. Exit the Tool:
To exit the tool, simply select option 00 from the menu.

